>
	<p>
		I'm Nikhil Pradhan. I build operating systems for places spreadsheets forgot.
	</p>
	<p>
		For the last six years, I've been an operator. I scaled multiple SMEs from
		<em>zero to seven-figure revenue</em> across India before founding ApiCare in
		Sikkim, India's only fully organic state. ApiCare is now an agri-tech venture
		operating with 125+ smallholder beekeepers and farmers under a World Bank
		RAMP partnership with the Government of Sikkim. We're building toward the
		EU export market.
	</p>
	<p>
		In 2025 I joined the Erasmus Mundus MBA program in Impact Entrepreneurship
		(EMMIE) — a fellowship that's taken me from Zagreb to Vilnius and, in
		September 2026, on to Liège. I graduate in December 2026.
	</p>
	<p>
		Alongside the MBA, I'm building <strong>FarmLedger</strong> — a WhatsApp-native
		AI traceability and credit-profile platform for the world's smallest farms.
		It uses multimodal AI to extract data from farmer-submitted photos and
		generate the kind of credit profiles a bank can actually read. We're
		shipping the MVP this quarter.
	</p>
	<h2>What's next</h2>
	<p>
		I'm moving toward Strategy &amp; Operations and AI Product Management roles
		at platform companies in Europe — Uber, Bolt, the marketplaces. I want to
		bring six years of operator instinct to teams building AI products that
		survive contact with reality. Available January 2027. EU work-eligible.
	</p>
